    • Constructor Detail

      • Property

        public Property(int nLocationIndex,
                int nColorIndex,
                int nPropertyIndex,
                int nPlayers)
        Constructor for a Property object. The OWNABLE_ID of this class's instances are based on their COLOR_INDEX and PROPERTY_INDEX attributes wherein the ID is equal to the color index * 10 + the property index.
        Parameters:
        nLocationIndex - Integer holding the location of an instance on a Board.
        nColorIndex - Integer holding the color type of an instance based on Reference.
        nPropertyIndex - Integer holding the property identification as is coordinated on Reference.
        nPlayers - Integer holding the number of players in the Game. Used in the calculation of the REQUIRED_FOOT_TRAFFIC attribute.

    • Method Detail

      • canBeDeveloped

        public boolean canBeDeveloped()
        Method that allows for development possibility checking. The checking is based on the nDevelopment, nFootTraffic, REQUIRED_FOOT_TRAFFIC, dTotalCollected, and pricing attributes of an instance.
        Returns:
        Boolean variable that is true when the instance can be developed. False, otherwise.

      • getPropertyRent

        public double getPropertyRent(Deck deck)
        Modified getter method for the dRent attribute of this class. The method takes into account the number of Property instances that the owner has and increases them accordingly. This method also removes the double rent chance cards, if any.
        Parameters:
        deck - Deck object to which the double rent chance card, if any, will be discarded.
        Returns:
        Double-precision floating point value that holds the amount to be paid.
